# Component Conventions

This repo is an early-stage UI reference for PaxPax Historia UI. Build in any order — no design-system phases.

## Rules

1. **One file = one component** in its own folder when non-trivial: `components/SettingRow/SettingRow.tsx`
2. **Props-first:** put anything that can change into props (label, icon, onClick, variant, isActive)
3. **Prefer one component + props over near-duplicates:** if two pieces differ only by role, position, or optional behavior (e.g. button vs link row, left vs right control), use a **single component** with props or a discriminated union — not two files with copy-pasted markup. Split only when structure or lifecycle genuinely diverges.
4. **Composition:** compose screens from small components; avoid 400-line monolith JSX
5. **Hard-code first, extract later:** a hex color in a component is OK; extract to a CSS variable or `variant` prop after 3+ repeats
6. **Theme:** use Tailwind `dark:` and CSS variables in `globals.css` when colors stabilize — not required on day one
7. **Responsive — desktop-first:** desktop layout in base classes; overrides via `max-xl:`, `max-lg:`, `max-md:` (not mobile-first `sm:` as default)
8. **Custom components only** — no HeroUI, shadcn, or other UI libraries
9. **No pre-built stubs** — add components only when building a real screen
10. **Icon hit targets** — clickable icons use at least **24×24px** hitbox (`ICON_HITBOX_CLASS` from `@/lib/icon-hitbox`); icon graphic stays centered inside
11. **Transitions** — use tokens from `@/lib/transitions` + CSS vars in `globals.css`; list in `variables.ts` for UI Kit
12. **Panel patterns** — drill-down panels split **shell size** (`@/lib/panelShell`) from **page slides** (`@/lib/panelNavigation`). Shell reacts to layout context (open/close, height mode, resize); navigation reacts to route forward/back only. Never couple their timing — see AGENTS.md § Panel patterns

## Panel patterns (detail)

When building an expanding panel with internal drill-down:

- **`useAnimatedPanelShell`** — shell size only (open/close, height mode, resize). `panelSizeTransitionClass` + px height.
- **`usePanelNavigation` + `getPanelNavigateTransition`** — step 2+ body page slide (`fast`, always X). Forward: new page enters left→right, old exits right.
- **`getMainMenuRevealMotion`** — step 1 title + rows (`medium`; mobile Y, desktop X). **`getSubPageRevealMotion`** — breadcrumbs (always X, keyed by direction).
- **Accordion** (`settingsMenuAccordionTransition`) — desktop-only in-place expand; not page nav.
- Reference: `SettingsMenu/` + `MobileTopControls/`. See AGENTS.md animation tier table.


Many parts of this repo are **UI placeholders** — simplified stand-ins for layout and visuals, not production behavior.

- Example: `GameScreen` uses a static `<img>` for the map; production Pax Historia uses a live interactive map.
- Placeholders may use static assets, hard-coded copy, or empty handlers.
- When building or documenting, note placeholder status (in code comments sparingly, and in `HANDOFF.md` inventory).
- In production handoff, placeholders are either **ignored** (real system already exists) or **replaced** (keep layout/styling, wire real data).

Do not over-engineer placeholder implementations — keep them minimal unless the user asks for more.

## Stack reminders

- TypeScript, Next.js App Router, Tailwind CSS v4, `motion`, `next-themes`
- Font: Poppins only (via `next/font`)
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/cn` for class names
- Add `'use client'` when using motion or browser-only APIs

## When advising — ask before assuming

Do not impose token/component phases. Suggest extraction only when a pattern repeats. Reference screenshots in `docs/reference/`.

**Ask the user** (briefly, 1–2 focused questions) when:

- Component **purpose or boundary** is unclear — e.g. is this a one-off screen section or a reusable pattern?
- Two components look **similar** and might be merged, split, or share a base — prefer **one component + props** unless structure truly diverges; propose merge before adding a sibling file
- Something looks like it should be **dynamic in production** but you're unsure what to placeholder — confirm what to mock vs skip
- **Naming or folder placement** is ambiguous — e.g. `patterns/` vs `components/`, screen-specific vs shared
- You notice **overlap with production concerns** (map, auth, game state) — clarify this repo stays visual-only

Share concerns openly: duplication, unclear props API, missing responsive behavior, or anything that would confuse a future integrator. Update `HANDOFF.md` inventory when adding non-trivial components.

## UI inspection (dev-only)

Tools for visually inspecting this repo while building — **not part of game UI** and not intended for production handoff.

1. **`DevThemeToggle`** — fixed bottom-center Light/Dark switch (in root layout). Use it to compare themes quickly.
2. **`/ui-kit` route** — living catalog of components, tokens, utilities, and dev tools with props, values, and live previews.

**When adding or changing UI building blocks**, always update:

- `src/lib/ui-kit/registry.ts` — metadata (name, path, category, props, values, notes, `viewportToggle`)
- `src/lib/ui-kit/variables.ts` — global CSS variables (when adding tokens to `globals.css`) and transition tokens
- `src/components/dev/ui-kit/` — live preview for that entry (if previewable)
- `HANDOFF.md` — routes and component inventory

Registry categories (tabs): `general`, `icons`, `components`, `styles`, `dev`, plus a **Variables** tab from `variables.ts`.
Set optional `group` on each registry entry; section order per tab lives in `src/lib/ui-kit/groups.ts`.
Set `viewportToggle: true` on responsive components so UI Kit shows Desktop / Mobile preview.
Put shared class strings and visual patterns in **Styles**; keep color/motion tokens in **Variables**.
